  "description": "Following the success of the <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/game/vr-soccer-96\">first Actua Soccer game</a>, a sequel was likely. The game is fast-paced with more of an action than simulation feel, and an emphasis on ground play rather than heading.<br><br>A young <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/search/quick?developer=Michael+Owen\">Michael Owen</a> provides motion capture to produce realistic player motions and actions - the different builds and styles of players are taken into account. 64 top international teams are featured, as are 24 distinct stadiums, with weather conditions having both visible and noticeable playing effects.<br><br>This was one of the first games to feature 2-man commentary, with former England captain <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/developer/sheet/view/developerId,42634/\">Trevor Brooking</a> joining <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/developer/sheet/view/developerId,31968/\">Barry Davies</a> in the analytical role.",
